# QuickCode — mandatory agent rules

Read `AGENTS.md` at repo root for full detail. Summary:

## NEVER edit or create

- `*.g.cs` — DBML generated
- `*.qc.cs` — QuickCode scaffold
- `*.g.sql`
- `Views/Generated/**`

If the task requires changing generated behavior → edit `src/dbml_files/*.dbml` and regenerate, or add user `.cs` files. Do not patch `.g.cs` / `.qc.cs`.

## WHERE to put NEW user code

Use plain `.cs` / `.cshtml` (never `.g.cs` / `.qc.cs` for your code).

| Goal | Path |
|------|------|
| New API/entity/query from schema | `src/dbml_files/{Module}.dbml` → `quickcode generate` |
| Extend generated class | Same layer as `.g.cs` → new `{Name}Extensions.cs` with `partial class` |
| Register DI (services) | `SiteServiceRegistration.cs` in Api / Portal / Gateway / EventListener → `AddSiteCustomizations()` |
| Custom middleware | `SitePipelineConfiguration.cs` in same host → `ConfigureSitePipeline*` hooks |
| Business logic / handlers | `src/Modules/{Module}/Core/QuickCode.{Project}.{Module}.Application/` |
| Domain (non-DBML) | `src/Modules/{Module}/Core/QuickCode.{Project}.{Module}.Domain/` |
| Custom repository / store | `src/Modules/{Module}/Infrastructure/QuickCode.{Project}.{Module}.Persistence/` |
| Custom API controller | `src/Modules/{Module}/Presentation/QuickCode.{Project}.{Module}.Api/Controllers/` |
| Custom portal Razor | `src/Presentation/QuickCode.{Project}.Portal/Views/` — **not** `Views/Generated/` |
| Portal controllers/helpers | `src/Presentation/QuickCode.{Project}.Portal/Controllers/` or `Helpers/` |
| Gateway | `src/Presentation/QuickCode.{Project}.Gateway/` |
| Cross-module shared | `src/Common/QuickCode.{Project}.Common/` |
| Event listener | `src/Services/QuickCode.{Project}.EventListenerService/` |

`{Project}` = PascalCase site name. `{Module}` = module folder under `src/Modules/`.

Regen never deletes or overwrites existing user `.cs` files.
